import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the overall distribution of unemployment rates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='rate', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Max rate: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which location has the highest unemployment rate?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between location size and unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location Size')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('id').mean()
    data.plot(kind='bar', y='rate', legend=None)
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate by region?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region ID')
    plt.ylabel('Average Unemployment Rate')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('How has the unemployment rate changed over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
